Three ODM woman representatives have reiterated calls for NASA to endorse Raila Odinga&rsquo;s presidential bid. Florence Mutua (Busia), Gladys Wanga (Homa Bay), and Fatuma Ibrahim (Wajir) affirmed their support for Odinga, saying he was the most experienced among the four NASA principals. Speaking at the Busia Agricultural Centre during the presentation of affirmative action development cheques to women and youth groups, they urged local residents to vote in ODM leaders at all levels. &ldquo;Raila Amollo Odinga has fought for this country for long. He has been in the forefront of bringing about devolution and fighting against corruption,&rdquo; said Mutua. The sentiments were supported by Wanga and Ibrahim. ALSO READ: Three Wajir MPs ditch Opposition for Jubilee